        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1547",
        "content": "Brooms and dishcloths never could be as distasteful as they once had been, for Beth had presided over both, and something of her housewifely spirit seemed to linger around the little mop and the old brush, never thrown away.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-low",
